In [106]:
# Earned Medal Distribution based on top 15 participating countries
top_15 = athlete_region.Team.value_counts().sort_values(ascending=False).head(15)

# Calculate total medals for each of the top ten countries
medals = athlete_region[athlete_region['Team'].isin(top_15.index) & (athlete_region['Medal'] != 'N/A')].groupby('Team')['Medal'].count()

# Plot
plt.figure(figsize=(14, 8))  # Aspect ratio 1:1 for a circular pie chart
plt.pie(medals, labels=medals.index, colors=plt.cm.tab20.colors, autopct='%1.1f%%', startangle=140)
plt.title('Distribution of Medals Won by Top 15 Countries (1896-2016)')
plt.show()

# Women Pariticpation in Summer and Winter Olympics (1896-2016)
women_summer = athlete_region[(athlete_region.Sex == 'F')&(athlete_region.Season == 'Summer')]
sns.set(style='dark')
plt.figure(figsize=(20,10))
sns.countplot(x='Year', data=women_summer, palette="flare")
plt.title("Women Participation in Summer", fontsize=15)
plt.ylabel('Number of Participants')
plt.xticks(fontsize=15)
plt.yticks(fontsize=15)
plt.show()

# Height vs Weight of all Olympians
not_null = athlete_region[(athlete_region['Height'].notnull()) & (athlete_region['Weight'].notnull())]
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
sns.scatterplot(x='Height', y='Weight', data=not_null, hue='Sex', palette={'M': 'limegreen', 'F':'darkviolet'})
sns.regplot(x='Height', y='Weight', data=not_null, scatter=False, color='black')
plt.title('Height vs Weight of Olympic Participants')
plt.xlabel('Height')
plt.ylabel('Weight')
plt.show()

# Height vs Weight of Olympian Medalists
